verbose_text: We have also documented the pattern of expression of NR in the uterine natural killer cells (uNK), which represent a major fraction of the endometrial immune cell population, especially in the luteal phase and demonstrated that these cells express ERbeta and glucocorticoid receptor (GR) but not ERalpha or the progesterone receptor (PR).
